<li><a href="http://www.constitution.org/hs/ignore_state.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.constitution.org/hs/ignore_state.htm" rel="nofollow">The Right to Ignore the State</a> by Herbert Spencer.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.fordham.edu/halsall/mod/spencer-darwin.html" class="external text" title="http://www.fordham.edu/halsall/mod/spencer-darwin.html" rel="nofollow">Excerpts from <i>Progress: Its Law and Cause</i></a> available from the <a href="/wiki/Internet_Modern_History_Sourcebook" title="Internet Modern History Sourcebook" class="mw-redirect">Internet Modern History Sourcebook</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.fordham.edu/halsall/mod/spencer-darwin.html" class="external text" title="http://www.fordham.edu/halsall/mod/spencer-darwin.html" rel="nofollow">Modern History Sourcebook: Herbert Spencer: Social Darwinism, 1857</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.lewrockwell.com/orig3/long3.html" class="external text" title="http://www.lewrockwell.com/orig3/long3.html" rel="nofollow">"Herbert Spencer: The Defamation Continues"</a> - a vindication by <a href="/wiki/Roderick_T._Long" title="Roderick T. Long" class="mw-redirect">Roderick T. Long</a></li>
</ul>
